->Core Idea: Sliding Window + Frequency Counting
We want the smallest substring of s that contains all characters of t (including duplicates).

->Key observations:
1)Order does not matter
2)Characters can repeat
3)We must track how many times each character appears

->So we use:
1)A frequency map for characters in t
2)A sliding window over s
3)Two pointers: left and right

->Key Variables Explained
Variable	           Meaning
freq	        Stores how many times each char in t is still needed
count        	Number of characters matched so far
left        	Left pointer of the window
r	            Right pointer of the window
minl	        Length of the smallest valid window found
start       	Starting index of the minimum window

